        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Chronicles 1:5-16",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", because in him the genealogy was to be continued (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Genesis 10:2",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " note), so Isaac is now reserved until the other lines of descent from Abraham have been completed. The same principle gives the descendants of Esau a prior place to those of Jacob ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Chronicles 1:35-51",
